  "description": "Traditional tempering and slow simmering deepen the flavor so the meal tastes complete even with minimal oil. Vendakkai Kara Kuzhambu with Little Millet brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Heat oil in a kadai over medium heat. Add mustard, fenugreek, and curry leaves; once aromatic, add onion and cook 4 minutes until lightly colored.",
    "Add tomato, spice powders, and vegetable; cook 3 minutes until the tomato turns jammy and the masala coats the pieces.",
    "Pour in tamarind extract, 350 ml water, salt, and the cooked pulse accent if using. Simmer on medium-low heat for 14 to 16 minutes until the kuzhambu reduces slightly and the oil forms a thin sheen on top.",
    "Rest 5 minutes before serving over the grain so the acidity rounds out."
  ],
